      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 506: This method no longer guarantees execution on the main thread before instantiating and using `CallViewController`. The previous implementation wrapped the whole flow in `DispatchQueue.main.async`; after this change, any caller invoking `startOutgoingCall` from a background callback can create UIKit objects and mutate presentation-related state off-main, which can crash or cause racey UI behavior. Keep the early `placeCall` optimization, but preserve the main-thread boundary for view-controller creation and presentation.\n\n```suggestion\nDispatchQueue.main.async { [weak self] in\n    guard let self \u003d self else { return }\n\n    let callViewController \u003d CallViewController.instantiate(with: self.injectionBag)\n    callViewController.viewModel.placeCall(with: contactRingId,\n                                           userName: userName,\n                                           account: account,\n                                           isAudioOnly: isAudioOnly)\n\n    self.dismissAllModals { [weak self] in\n        guard let self \u003d self else { return }\n        self.popToSmartList()\n        self.navigateToConversationIfNeeded(for: contactRingId, account: account)\n        self.present(viewController: callViewController,\n                     withStyle: .fadeInOverFullScreen,\n                     withAnimation: false,\n                     withStateable: callViewController.viewModel)\n    }\n}\n```",
